Get 25% off your 1st Thrive Market order & a free gift: http://thrivemarket.com/bobbyIG

RECIPE:
1/2 red onion, diced
3 cloves garlic, minced
1 pound ground beef
12 ounces sliced baby bella mushrooms
8 ounces frozen stor fry veggies
17 ounces pre-cooked wild rice
2 eggs
Coconut aminos
Sriracha sauce
Toasted sesame oil
Ghee
Salt

Preheat a large non-stick pan over medium heat with 2 teaspoons of ghee. Add the dived red onion, a pinch of salt, and cook for 5 minutes. Add the garlic and cook another two minutes. Turn the heat up a little bit then add the ground beef, season with a pinch of salt, and break it up very well. Cook until almost all the way cooked through, then add 3 tablespoons coconut aminos, 1 teaspoon sriracha, and 1 teaspoon of sesame oil. Mix well and cook 3 minutes then check for seasoning and adjust if necessary. Remove beef mixture from pan.

Add another 2 teaspoons of ghee to the same pan over medium heat along with the sliced mushrooms and a pinch of salt. Cook for 8 minutes, or until the mushrooms are golden brown then add the frozen veggies. Cook for 5 minutes then add the cooked wild rice. Cook for 2 minutes then add 3 tablespoons coconut aminos, 1 teaspoon sriracha, and 1 teaspoon of sesame oil. Mix well and cook for 1 minute then check for seasoning. You may need more aminos or sriracha depending on your taste. Cook for 2 more minutes then make a well in the middle of the pan and cook the scrambled eggs. Mix everything together, add the meat back to the pan, and stir to combine. Serve the fried rice and enjoy!

Join Thrive Market & get 25% off your 1st order & a FREE gift: http://thrivemarket.com/bobbyIG

RECIPE: 
2 chicken breasts
1 teaspoon each cumin, turmeric, italian seasoning
Two 8 ounce packs of quinoa & brown rice
1 cup beef bone broth
1 cup grated cheddar cheese
salt & pepper 
Extra virgin olive oil

Pound the chicken breasts to make them a bit thinner and the same thickness from top to bottom. Make the spice rub by combining the cumin, turmeric, and Italian seasoning in a small bowl. Add a good pinch of salt and spice rub to each breast along with a drizzle of olive oil and rub the spices into the chicken, Flip and repeat. Let the chicken sit for 15 minutes at room temperature.

Meanwhile, preheat a large non-stick pan over medium heat along with 1 tablespoon of olive oil. Add both packs of brown rice and quinoa along with 1/2 teaspoon of salt and a few cracks of pepper. Mix well and cook for 3 minutes then add the bone broth and cook until most of it has evaporated, but the mixture is still wet. Add the cheese, lower the heat, and mix well. Cook another 3 minutes, adding more bone broth if the mixture is too dry. You want it to be wet and saucy like risotto. Remove from heat. 

To cook the chicken, preheat a cast iron pan just below medium-heat high heat with 2 tablespoons of olive oil. Once the pan is hot add the chicken breasts and press them into the pan. Cook for 5 minutes then flip and cook another 4 minutes. Only flip the chicken once. Remove the chicken and allow the breasts to rest for minutes until tin foil. 
Slice the chicken and lace it on top of the brothy quinoa and brown rice. Serve and enjoy!

RECIPE:
1/2 red onion, diced
3 cloves garlic, minced
1 pound ground beef
12 ounces sliced baby bella mushrooms
8 ounces frozen stor fry veggies
17 ounces pre-cooked wild rice
2 eggs
Coconut aminos
Sriracha sauce
Toasted sesame oil
Ghee
Salt

Preheat a large non-stick pan over medium heat with 2 teaspoons of ghee. Add the dived red onion, a pinch of salt, and cook for 5 minutes. Add the garlic and cook another two minutes. Turn the heat up a little bit then add the ground beef, season with a pinch of salt, and break it up very well. Cook until almost all the way cooked through, then add 3 tablespoons coconut aminos, 1 teaspoon sriracha, and 1 teaspoon of sesame oil. Mix well and cook 3 minutes then check for seasoning and adjust if necessary. Remove beef mixture from pan.

Add another 2 teaspoons of ghee to the same pan over medium heat along with the sliced mushrooms and a pinch of salt. Cook for 8 minutes, or until the mushrooms are golden brown then add the frozen veggies. Cook for 5 minutes then add the cooked wild rice. Cook for 2 minutes then add 3 tablespoons coconut aminos, 1 teaspoon sriracha, and 1 teaspoon of sesame oil. Mix well and cook for 1 minute then check for seasoning. You may need more aminos or sriracha depending on your taste. Cook for 2 more minutes then make a well in the middle of the pan and cook the scrambled eggs. Mix everything together, add the meat back to the pan, and stir to combine. Serve the fried rice and enjoy!

node.text:
@rosehoneyp made cauliflower hummus and it was tasty!!
RECIPE:
1 medium size head cauliflower
4 cloves garlic
1/2 cup tahini
zest & juice of half lemon
1 tablespoon extra virgin olive oil
3/4 teaspoons salt
Few cracks of pepper

Bring a medium size pot of water to a boil and season with 1 tablespoon of salt. Meanwhile, cut the cauliflower florets into large bite size pieces and take the garlic out of the skin. Add to the boiling water and cook for 10 minutes. The cauliflower should be soft, but not mushy.

Drain well and add to a blender with the tahini, lemon zest & juice, olive oil, salt, and pepper. Blend on high for 1 minute, adding a touch more water if the consistency is too thick. Check for seasoning and enjoy!

RECIPE: 
2 chicken breasts
1 teaspoon each cumin, turmeric, italian seasoning
Two 8 ounce packs of quinoa & brown rice
1 cup beef bone broth
1 cup grated cheddar cheese
salt & pepper 
Extra virgin olive oil

Pound the chicken breasts to make them a bit thinner and the same thickness from top to bottom. Make the spice rub by combining the cumin, turmeric, and Italian seasoning in a small bowl. Add a good pinch of salt and spice rub to each breast along with a drizzle of olive oil and rub the spices into the chicken, Flip and repeat. Let the chicken sit for 15 minutes at room temperature.

Meanwhile, preheat a large non-stick pan over medium heat along with 1 tablespoon of olive oil. Add both packs of brown rice and quinoa along with 1/2 teaspoon of salt and a few cracks of pepper. Mix well and cook for 3 minutes then add the bone broth and cook until most of it has evaporated, but the mixture is still wet. Add the cheese, lower the heat, and mix well. Cook another 3 minutes, adding more bone broth if the mixture is too dry. You want it to be wet and saucy like risotto. Remove from heat. 

To cook the chicken, preheat a cast iron pan just below medium-heat high heat with 2 tablespoons of olive oil. Once the pan is hot add the chicken breasts and press them into the pan. Cook for 5 minutes then flip and cook another 4 minutes. Only flip the chicken once. Remove the chicken and allow the breasts to rest for minutes until tin foil. 
Slice the chicken and lace it on top of the brothy quinoa and brown rice. Serve and enjoy!
